** Jem Health is a successful and growing local company that aims to provide high quality pre-employment / occupational health assessment services to our clients with an overarching goal to promote a safe work place. Through our consistent quality, evidence based assessments and caring about what we do, we help both the individual prospective employees, and the employing company to reduce their risk of harm in the workplace. **

** THE OPPORTUNITY **

An opportunity has presented for a highly motivated and enthusiastic Exercise
Physiologist or Physiotherapist to join the Jem Health team as an Occupational
Health Assessor (OHA). Your role will be to provide exceptional service,
consistent quality and attention to detail in the delivery of employment-
related health assessments and occupational health initiatives.

We are currently seeking applications for our Spring Hill, QLD office. We can
be flexible and work around study, second jobs and home commitments for the
right applicant(s) and are open to a full time role or a couple of part time
roles.

Jem Health, Health Assessor staff are responsible for the following key areas
of responsibility (not limited to):

\- Occupational Health Assessments including pre-employment medicals,
audiometry, spirometry, ECGs, drug screening, functional capacity assessments
and fitness testing.

\- Timely and accurate reporting

\- High level compliance and observation of privacy act

\- Worker health checks and ergonomics

\- General administration

\- Monitoring and maintaining stock levels & equipment

\- Health and wellness projects, initiatives, training and promotion

\- Contribute to client relationship management, continuous improvement and
business growth initiatives

\- Commitment and compliance to strong safety culture

** THE SUCCESSFUL APPLICANT **

In addition to demonstrating a genuine passion for health and safety - the
successful applicant will need to demonstrate the following:

  * Bachelor degree in Health Science, Physio or Ex Phys or similar health discipline 
  * High interest in occupational health 
  * Registration/accreditation with AHPRA / ESSA 
  * Current and maintained First Aid and CPR 
  * Exceptional interpersonal skills and demonstrated ability to build rapport 
  * Intermediate to strong computer skills including demonstrated proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite and using two screens. 
  * Advanced written and verbal communication skills 
  * Willingness to learn and grow 
  * Team contributor 
  * High level of professionalism 
  * A very high level of care and attention to detail 
  * Exceptional time management, organisation and ability to work autonomously & as a team. 
  * High level of emotional intelligence 

Desirable but not essential Criteria:

  * Experience/exposure to Occupational Health 
  * Certificate IV or Diploma in WHS 
  * Experience or Qualification in Audiometry 
  * Experience or Qualification in Spirometry 
  * Experience or Qualification in Drug and Alcohol Screening 
  * Drivers licence 

All applicants must have the right to work in Australia

** THE WORKPLACE **

Jem Health prides itself on a culture of respect and providing a supportive
and progressive work environment where our people are important . You would be
part of a team of medical and allied health professionals working together to
deliver second to none service value to our clients. In addition, an
attractive, above award wage will be offered to the successful applicant in
line with skills and experiences.

We are seeking expressions of interest for roles to work M â€“ F with various
office hours shift availability

** THE APPLICATION PROCESS **

If you are ready and keen to be a valued contributor to the Jem Health team in
an Occupational Health Assessor role, don't miss this opportunity to join a
team that shares your passion for people, health and quality service.

Please forward application, confirming your preference for full time or part
time and addressing the selection criteria to [ [email protected]  ](/cdn-
cgi/l/email-protection#e182809384849392a18b848c8984808d9589cf828e8ccf8094)

New graduates are encouraged to apply but please include academic record with
your application.

Recruitment and selection process will require applicants to provide Police
Clearance, participate in a face to face and/ or online- based interview and
assessment process, and successfully complete a pre-employment medical and
functional assessment, drug and alcohol screen and reference checks.

Both new graduates and experienced health professionals are encouraged to
apply.

